H1> Managing downloads

P> The Downloads admin organises files into categories ("download parents") and links them to images and descriptions for the public download page.

SHOT> downloads/admin-download.png | List view of downloads grouped by parent category

Q> What's a download parent?
A> A parent groups your downloads into categories (e.g. "Documentation", "Themes", "Tools"). Visitors browse by category, which keeps long lists manageable.

Q> I want to add a download but the file doesn't appear in the list – why?
A> Only files placed in `e107_files/downloads/` show up in the dropdown. Copy the file there and it will appear. Images for the download work the same way but live in `e107_files/downloadimages/`.

TIP> If you maintain many downloads, consider uploading via SFTP/SSH directly into `e107_files/downloads/` rather than the web uploader – it's faster and bypasses PHP's `upload_max_filesize` limit.

WARN> Files placed in `e107_files/downloads/` are publicly downloadable through e107 once linked. Do not stage private documents in that folder.
